          aside
            pre
              <br>
              |In the late nineties IE rapidly overtook netscape in market penetration. 1st browser war saw ms throwing money
              |at IE, integrating the browser into their OS and dominating the market.
              <br>
              |It was during this time that MS Even though we had an establised method for evolving standards
              |ms went there own way.
              <br>
              |For developers this was awful. You needed to spend most of your time developing for the browser with the
              |largest audience. Remember those "Best Viewed in IE badges.
              <br>
              |Developing solely for IEs Proprietary standards broke most of the bullets we previously mentioned
              |and would bake in problems later. Even today there are many applications that only work in IE6 because
              |that specific version had a Proprietary feature that was coded too.

          
